{"title":"Onshore wind: call for evidence","public_updated_at":"2012-09-19T23:00:00Z","details":{"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><h3 id=\"part-a-community-engagement-and-benefits\">Part A: Community engagement and benefits</h3>\n\n<h3 id=\"part-b-costs\">Part B: Costs</h3>\n\n<p>These two calls for evidence on onshore wind energy are being issued in parallel and seek information on :</p>\n\n<p><strong>Part A:</strong> the different types of engagement activities being carried out between onshore wind developers and communities and the various community benefit packages offered across the UK and internationally. This will be used to examine how communities can have more of a say over, and receive greater economic and wider social benefits from hosting onshore wind farms.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Part B:</strong> latest data on pre-development costs, capital costs , operating costs and financial costs of onshore wind development in the UK . This will be used to identify any changes to the costs faced by developers/investors and operators of onshore wind, using the Renewables Obligation Banding Review Govt Response data as a baseline.</p>\n\n<p>We invite interested parties to submit comments and evidence in response to either or both of these two calls.</p>\n\n<p>Where possible please use the templates provided to record your responses and evidence.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"contact-us\">Contact us</h2>\n\n<p>Tel:\n     0300 068 6194\nEmail:\n    <a href=\"mailto:onshorewind@decc.gsi.gov.uk\">onshorewind@decc.gsi.gov.uk</a>\nPost:\n    Renewables Delivery team</p>\n\n<p>Department of Energy and Climate Change 4th Floor Area A,</p>\n\n<p>3 Whitehall Place,</p>\n\n<p>London</p>\n\n<p>SW1A2AW</p>\n\n<p><strong>Please note:</strong> An update has been issued (25 October 2012) to the Part B Call for Evidence document on Costs. This corrects errors in the cost data presented for ‘variable opex’, ‘insurance’ and ‘connection and UoS charges’ in Table 2 of Annex A.</p>\n</div>","closing_date":"